Foxfingers stood still, in his left hand was the vial of energeon which he
carefully kept between the Predacon weapons and himself. his right hand
rumaged through the various side pockets where he kept his tricks hoping
he'd miscounted while useing them. "I know how much you hate Maximals, but I
also know that you can be civilized enough to know what benefits yous
squad." A blank look took over his face followed quickly by the sly grin of
a poker player raising on a pair of deuces, "Is it really worth putting
every bot in this place at risk to destroy me?" he shook the vial a little
bit almost dareing the Predacons to try and fire around it. "By now I'm sure
you found a temporary cure for the virus, you may even find a cure, maybe
theres even a chance that I'm bluffing and there is no virus in the vial."
the bold thief found himself being braver than he'd ever been. Before he'd
given himself up for dead, now he found himself at a stand still keeping
himself alive. "Right now I'm sure we all know the question going through
your processors." he crouched a little making himself a harder target,
(Sorry can't resist) "That question you're asking yourself is DO I FEEL
LUCKY?" the fox again paused to buy himself a few more moments of life,
"Well DO YA?"
